'Cause it's not too late.

03:50.857 --> 03:52.511
It's never too late.

03:52.554 --> 03:54.687
♪

03:54.730 --> 03:57.820
Another one
off the board.

04:01.476 --> 04:03.783
Good night,
John.

04:03.826 --> 04:05.741
Night, June.

04:10.790 --> 04:13.749
[Creaking]

04:14.837 --> 04:17.840
[Thumping]

04:23.063 --> 04:26.762
[Dishes clattering]

04:28.460 --> 04:31.332
[Bottles clinking]

04:33.552 --> 04:37.991
[Clattering]

04:38.034 --> 04:40.254
June!John!
Are you okay?

04:40.298 --> 04:42.604
[Electricity buzzing]

04:42.648 --> 04:44.867
Yeah.

04:53.789 --> 04:55.225
What is that?

04:59.273 --> 05:02.102
Do you see anything?

05:02.145 --> 05:04.409
It's another room.

05:04.452 --> 05:06.802
What?

05:15.768 --> 05:22.035
♪

05:24.820 --> 05:28.824
[Gate creaks]

05:28.868 --> 05:38.834
♪

05:38.878 --> 05:48.278
♪

05:48.322 --> 05:58.245
♪

05:58.288 --> 06:08.255
♪

06:08.298 --> 06:10.083
♪

06:10.126 --> 06:12.520
John...

06:12.564 --> 06:15.871
I know.
What is this place?

06:18.352 --> 06:20.485
Teddy.

06:20.528 --> 06:24.663
This is where he killed
all those women.

06:24.706 --> 06:28.275
♪

06:28.318 --> 06:31.539
It's where
it all started.

06:32.758 --> 06:34.324
We...

06:34.368 --> 06:37.197
We could never
find it.

06:37.240 --> 06:39.939
It was under our feet
the whole time.

06:39.982 --> 06:43.464
He's gone,
John.

06:43.508 --> 06:46.859
He can't do this to anyone
ever again.

06:46.902 --> 06:48.687
♪

06:48.730 --> 06:52.560
So let's just
seal this room up

06:52.604 --> 06:54.823
and pretend
it doesn't exist.

06:54.867 --> 07:04.006
♪

07:04.050 --> 07:06.748
It's not too late.

07:06.792 --> 07:09.751
It's never too late.

07:09.795 --> 07:19.761
♪

07:19.805 --> 07:26.507
♪

07:28.944 --> 07:32.208
[Electricity crackles]

07:32.644 --> 07:35.081
We should
close it up.

07:35.124 --> 07:36.778
No.

07:36.822 --> 07:39.433
I think I'm gonna leave it open
for a little while.

07:39.477 --> 07:40.565
John --
I have questions.

07:40.608 --> 07:42.523
Had 'em
close to 40 years.

07:42.567 --> 07:44.525
The answers
might be in here.

07:44.569 --> 07:47.049
Theodore Maddox
killed 23 women.

07:47.093 --> 07:49.008
At least that's how many
he confessed to.

07:49.051 --> 07:50.923
Yeah, you don't have to
relive it all for me.

07:50.966 --> 07:52.272
No way
I can forget it, June.

07:52.315 --> 07:54.579
The women --
he did the same thing to them

07:54.622 --> 07:56.232
that he was doing
after he escaped prison.

07:56.276 --> 07:57.538
Embalming 'em
so they'd never have

07:57.582 --> 07:59.018
what he called
a new beginning.

07:59.061 --> 08:00.802
Problem is,
we could never find the place

08:00.846 --> 08:02.674
where he was doing
the embalming.

08:04.284 --> 08:06.460
Which is why he was able
to continue as long as he did.

08:06.504 --> 08:08.027
You still stopped him.

08:08.070 --> 08:09.419
Only for a spell.

08:09.463 --> 08:11.596
He still got
what he wanted, June.

08:11.639 --> 08:13.467
John, I don't think
going over all this

08:13.511 --> 08:16.078
is going to
help anyone.

08:16.122 --> 08:18.994
It might.
What do you mean?

08:20.474 --> 08:21.780
I didn't
find 'em all.

08:22.998 --> 08:24.043
Find what?

08:24.086 --> 08:26.175
I said we knew he killed
23 women,

08:26.219 --> 08:28.264
but we only found
22 bodies.

08:28.308 --> 08:30.658
His last victim,
Cindy Hawkins,

08:30.702 --> 08:32.268
the one whose purse
I planted,

08:32.312 --> 08:34.009
he finally admitted
he killed her.

08:34.053 --> 08:35.576
It's what cracked
the whole thing open.

08:35.620 --> 08:37.491
But I never found
her body.

08:37.535 --> 08:40.059
I looked that girl's mama
square in the eye,

08:40.102 --> 08:42.061
and I promised her
I'd help her bury her baby,

08:42.104 --> 08:44.063
promised her I'd help give her
the ending she deserved.

08:44.106 --> 08:45.455
But I was never
able to.

08:45.499 --> 08:47.893
You tried.
That's what counts.

08:47.936 --> 08:49.677
I made a promise
I couldn't keep back then.

08:49.721 --> 08:51.897
But maybe I can now.

08:51.940 --> 08:54.464
Maybe something in here
will help me find where she is.

08:54.508 --> 08:55.901
John,
even if you figure it out,

08:55.944 --> 08:57.206
you can't leave here.

08:57.250 --> 09:00.122
[Creaking, rumbling]

09:00.166 --> 09:02.777
We may not
have a choice.

09:04.605 --> 09:06.825
How are
those suits coming?

09:08.696 --> 09:11.264
Still trying
to make them airtight.

09:11.307 --> 09:12.700
If we ever
go up there,

09:12.744 --> 09:14.659
we can't risk
breathing in any particles.

09:14.702 --> 09:16.051
How long till you think
they'll be done?

09:16.095 --> 09:17.313
It's not just
the suits.

09:17.357 --> 09:18.532
I mean,
once these are done,

09:18.576 --> 09:19.707
we need
some kind of airlock --

09:19.751 --> 09:21.143
a go-between from outside
to in here

09:21.187 --> 09:23.493
so we don't drag anything
back in.

09:23.537 --> 09:25.365
Why would we
come back?

09:27.019 --> 09:29.325
We don't know what kind of
radiation is up there.

09:29.369 --> 09:30.849
There are some types

09:30.892 --> 09:32.894
that suits might not even
protect against.

09:32.938 --> 09:34.287
And if there are?

09:34.330 --> 09:35.810
Well,
I'm not an expert,

09:35.854 --> 09:37.638
but from
what I've read...

09:39.901 --> 09:43.252
...it'll be
a lot safer then.

09:44.906 --> 09:47.735
Well, uh, you keep
working on the suits.

09:47.779 --> 09:49.171
I'll start
shoring things up,

09:49.215 --> 09:50.956
buy us some time
in case we can't venture out.

09:50.999 --> 09:52.653
I think I saw some twobys
next door.

09:52.697 --> 09:55.308
Mm.

09:57.179 --> 09:58.920
I'm sorry,
June.

09:58.964 --> 10:01.575
I know
I'm not the Dorie

10:01.619 --> 10:03.577
you thought you'd be
spending your days with.

10:03.621 --> 10:05.971
I am happy to be
where I am.

10:06.014 --> 10:08.626
I hope
you feel the same.[Chuckles]

10:08.669 --> 10:09.931
You're talking
to the guy

10:09.975 --> 10:12.934
who lived on his own up there
for decades.

10:12.978 --> 10:14.370
This...

10:14.414 --> 10:16.198
This ain't so bad.

10:27.819 --> 10:30.473
[Sighs]

10:30.517 --> 10:35.565
♪

10:35.609 --> 10:40.701
♪

10:40.745 --> 10:42.790
John?

10:42.834 --> 10:45.140
Have you seen
the scissors?

10:45.184 --> 10:47.752
♪

10:47.795 --> 10:49.579
[Hammer pounding]

10:49.623 --> 10:51.538
That oughta do it.

10:51.581 --> 10:52.582
[Electricity buzzing]

10:52.626 --> 10:55.629
Oh,
just in time.

10:55.673 --> 10:57.500
Lights out?

10:57.544 --> 11:00.025
♪

11:00.068 --> 11:02.767
[Sighs]

11:03.768 --> 11:05.813
Yeah.

11:05.857 --> 11:09.034
Little late
for pedaling.

11:10.209 --> 11:12.602
Time to hit
the hay.

11:17.172 --> 11:20.175
Another one
off the board.

11:21.437 --> 11:23.004
Where's the hooch?

11:23.048 --> 11:26.442
It all got smashed,
along with all the preserves

11:26.486 --> 11:28.662
and everything else
on the shelf.

11:28.706 --> 11:30.185
Plenty of Tang left.

11:32.274 --> 11:34.624
That's alright.

11:34.668 --> 11:36.888
Night, John.

11:41.849 --> 11:44.417
Night, June.

11:51.250 --> 11:54.906
[Metal creaking]

11:57.343 --> 12:00.563
[Sighs]

12:00.607 --> 12:05.046
♪

12:05.090 --> 12:10.573
[Groans]

12:10.617 --> 12:20.583
♪

12:20.627 --> 12:30.593
♪

12:30.637 --> 12:39.646
♪

12:39.689 --> 12:43.476
[Electricity buzzing]

12:43.519 --> 12:51.049
♪

12:51.092 --> 12:53.834
[Lid creaks]

12:53.878 --> 12:55.444
♪

12:55.488 --> 12:58.012
[Paper rustling]

12:58.056 --> 13:08.022
♪

13:08.066 --> 13:18.032
♪

13:18.076 --> 13:25.344
♪

13:25.387 --> 13:27.868
Cindy...

13:27.912 --> 13:30.740
I'm sorry
I didn't keep my promise.

13:30.784 --> 13:33.743
[Electricity buzzing]

13:33.787 --> 13:37.138
[Creaking]

13:37.182 --> 13:39.575
June?

13:39.619 --> 13:41.969
[Creaking continues]

13:46.408 --> 13:48.193
June.

13:50.325 --> 13:53.067
[Creaking continues]

14:03.817 --> 14:08.343
[Creaking continues]

14:14.262 --> 14:16.177
[Pounding on door]

14:16.221 --> 14:18.353
Is someone up there?

14:19.441 --> 14:21.574
[Muffled voice]

14:26.709 --> 14:28.798
Woman:
[Echoing] Help me!

14:28.842 --> 14:36.763
♪

14:41.202 --> 14:43.770
[Door opens]

14:48.601 --> 14:53.084
[Breathing heavily]

15:23.679 --> 15:26.247
Hello?

15:26.291 --> 15:28.815
Anybody out there?

15:28.858 --> 15:31.296
[Breathing heavily]

15:42.742 --> 15:45.875
This the beginning
you had in mind, Teddy?

15:45.919 --> 15:48.269
♪

15:48.313 --> 15:52.056
[Walker growling]

16:11.379 --> 16:13.642
Dakota.

16:13.686 --> 16:15.427
You poor girl.

16:15.470 --> 16:17.995
The only one I couldn't save.

16:19.474 --> 16:22.651
[Growling stops]

16:22.695 --> 16:25.480
[Breathing heavily]

16:25.524 --> 16:27.482
Help...me.

16:33.010 --> 16:36.013
Help me.

16:39.755 --> 16:42.280
Help me.

16:42.323 --> 16:44.325
What's wrong?

16:44.369 --> 16:46.545
You shouldn't be out here
without protection.

16:46.588 --> 16:49.852
Help me.

16:49.896 --> 16:52.942
[Breathing heavily]

16:53.943 --> 16:56.555
Woman:
Help me.

16:56.598 --> 16:57.947
Help me.

16:57.991 --> 16:59.732
♪

16:59.775 --> 17:01.603
[Gasps]

17:01.647 --> 17:04.389
You promised.

17:04.432 --> 17:06.608
Cindy.[Fabric rips]

17:06.652 --> 17:08.915
[Gunshot]

17:08.958 --> 17:10.917
John,
what's going on?!

17:10.960 --> 17:12.310
You shot her!

17:12.353 --> 17:14.486
Who?!
What are you talking about?!

17:14.529 --> 17:16.879
♪

17:16.923 --> 17:18.881
[Breathing heavily]

17:18.925 --> 17:21.536
John?
[Gun clicks]

17:21.580 --> 17:26.759
♪

17:26.802 --> 17:28.717
Get inside!

17:28.761 --> 17:30.632
♪

17:30.676 --> 17:32.112
[Door closes]

17:36.029 --> 17:38.205
Did you lock
the hatch?Think it'll hold?

17:38.249 --> 17:39.989
You're asking
the wrong man.

17:40.033 --> 17:41.600
Who were they?You saw 'em
longer than I did.

17:41.643 --> 17:43.210
Easy.
Don't move.
Hey,
I can get myself out.

17:43.254 --> 17:44.646
No, John,
but I need to check.I'm fine.

17:44.690 --> 17:46.170
Yeah, but I am not! Alright?
It's not just about you,

17:46.213 --> 17:48.215
and it is not just about
those contaminants

17:48.259 --> 17:49.651
or whoever the hell
was up there.

17:49.695 --> 17:51.349
I need to make sure
you weren't bit.

17:51.392 --> 17:52.741
I wasn't.
John --

17:52.785 --> 17:54.787
I wasn't!But you could've been!

17:55.918 --> 17:57.659
It's just a scratch.

17:58.791 --> 18:00.184
What were you doing
up there?

18:00.227 --> 18:02.751
Why were you up there
all by yourself?

18:02.795 --> 18:05.406
I heard her.
She was calling me.Who?

18:05.450 --> 18:07.800
I know
what it's gonna sound like.

18:07.843 --> 18:09.149
Who, John?

18:10.237 --> 18:12.457
The girl
I never found.

18:14.502 --> 18:16.025
I don't understand,
John.

18:16.069 --> 18:18.506
I know what it sounds like,
but she was calling me.

18:18.550 --> 18:20.813
I mean, I didn't know
if she was the one calling me,

18:20.856 --> 18:22.597
but I heard a voice.

18:22.641 --> 18:24.033
So I went up,

18:24.077 --> 18:26.253
and there she was,
plain as day.

18:28.386 --> 18:30.649
Are you sure
you're okay?

18:30.692 --> 18:32.781
Are you sure
you didn't hit your head?

18:32.825 --> 18:34.609
I know
what I saw, dammit.

18:40.920 --> 18:44.445
I put Dakota out of
her torment when I was up there.

18:44.489 --> 18:47.187
What Teddy did
to the state of the state --

18:47.231 --> 18:48.928
it ain't pretty,
June.

18:48.971 --> 18:51.017
We shoulda stopped him.But we didn't.

18:51.060 --> 18:52.714
John,
these decisions,

18:52.758 --> 18:54.847
going up there,
we need to make them together.I know.

18:54.890 --> 18:56.370
I just...

18:56.414 --> 18:58.242
I won't
do it again.

19:00.113 --> 19:02.115
What are you
looking for?

19:02.159 --> 19:05.162
Ah, thought a drink
might take the edge off.

19:05.205 --> 19:08.034
I told you --
we lost all the whiskey.Are you sure?

19:08.077 --> 19:10.471
One thing I know about Teddy --
he liked to have a good time

19:10.515 --> 19:12.908
when he wasn't causing a bad one
for somebody else.

19:12.952 --> 19:15.302
That's why he had
as much as he did down here.

19:15.346 --> 19:17.261
How did you know
how much he had down here?

19:17.304 --> 19:19.611
Can't ration
without knowing.

19:19.654 --> 19:21.874
I know,
but that was my job.

19:23.049 --> 19:25.747
John, have you been drinking
without me knowing?

19:26.792 --> 19:28.707
Here and there.
How much?

19:28.750 --> 19:29.969
I didn't keep track.

19:30.012 --> 19:31.927
And before,
when you were up there?

19:31.971 --> 19:34.191
I was alone a lot,
June.

19:34.234 --> 19:35.931
John,
I need you to tell me

19:35.975 --> 19:38.195
exactly how much
you were drinking up there.

19:40.153 --> 19:41.894
Half a bottle a day?

19:41.937 --> 19:43.722
Whatever I could find.

19:43.765 --> 19:45.724
And down here?

19:45.767 --> 19:47.291
A drink
here and there.

19:47.334 --> 19:49.510
It wasn't just
the night caps.

19:49.554 --> 19:50.946
I just...

19:50.990 --> 19:53.297
I thought there was enough
to get us through.

19:56.343 --> 19:59.085
Your hands
are shaking.

19:59.128 --> 20:01.740
When was the last time
you had a drink?

20:01.783 --> 20:03.089
Day before last.

20:03.132 --> 20:05.483
Before
the ceiling collapsed.

20:05.526 --> 20:06.788
[Clattering]

20:08.355 --> 20:10.183
Think it's
those masked folks?

20:10.227 --> 20:11.924
Doesn't sound like
the dead.

20:11.967 --> 20:13.534
[Sighs]

20:13.578 --> 20:16.189
Picked a helluva time
to go cold turkey.

20:16.233 --> 20:19.323
You don't suppose those
masked fellas are friendly.

20:19.366 --> 20:20.802
They don't sound friendly
to me.

20:20.846 --> 20:22.761
John, this is why I didn't
want you on that radio.

20:22.804 --> 20:24.153
Man:
Enough of this.

20:24.197 --> 20:25.720
We know you're listening.

20:25.764 --> 20:27.331
Open that door and let us in.

20:27.374 --> 20:29.202
This doesn't
have to get ugly...

20:29.246 --> 20:30.508
We should
say something.

20:30.551 --> 20:32.727
We know you're in there.

20:32.771 --> 20:34.381
I'm gonna have to
shore that up.

20:35.556 --> 20:37.428
We can't just
ignore them.

20:37.471 --> 20:38.951
John,
you're in no position to fight,

20:38.994 --> 20:40.257
and it's only
gonna get worse.

20:40.300 --> 20:41.997
You think
I don't know that?

20:42.041 --> 20:43.477
[Sighs]

20:43.521 --> 20:45.610
[Creaking]

20:45.653 --> 20:48.787
How long
will it last?
DTs?
Couple days.

20:48.830 --> 20:50.223
Fever, sweats,

20:50.267 --> 20:52.356
you may hear and see
more than you did up there.

20:57.535 --> 20:59.363
[Pounding]

21:03.062 --> 21:06.195
[Pounding continues][John sighs]

21:06.500 --> 21:07.719
[The Mamas and the Papas'
"California Dreamin'" plays]

21:07.762 --> 21:09.982
♪ Got down on my knees

21:10.025 --> 21:11.766
♪ And I pretend to pray

21:11.810 --> 21:13.986
♪ I pretend to pray

21:14.029 --> 21:16.510
♪ You know the preacher
likes the cold ♪

21:16.554 --> 21:18.425
♪ Preacher likes the cold

21:18.469 --> 21:20.819
♪ He knows I'm gonna stay

21:20.862 --> 21:23.212
♪ Knows I'm gonna stay

21:23.256 --> 21:24.779
♪ California dreamin'

21:24.823 --> 21:27.434
♪ California dreamin'

21:27.478 --> 21:29.784
♪ On such a winter's day

21:29.828 --> 21:33.353
♪

21:33.397 --> 21:41.622
[Switch clicks,
electricity buzzing]

21:41.666 --> 21:45.017
♪

21:45.060 --> 21:49.021
[Woman whimpers]

21:49.064 --> 21:51.632
♪

21:51.676 --> 22:01.642
♪

22:01.686 --> 22:05.254
♪

22:05.298 --> 22:08.780
John,
help me, please.

22:08.823 --> 22:10.434
♪

22:10.477 --> 22:12.914
Hurry.
He's going to come back.

22:12.958 --> 22:15.177
You're not really here.

22:15.221 --> 22:17.441
This isn't really now.

22:17.484 --> 22:19.225
John, please...

22:19.268 --> 22:27.102
♪

22:27.146 --> 22:29.627
What do I have to do
for you to leave me alone?

22:29.670 --> 22:31.280
♪

22:31.324 --> 22:34.936
Keep your promise.

22:34.980 --> 22:36.808
Find me.

22:36.851 --> 22:42.030
♪

22:42.074 --> 22:43.467
June: John?

22:44.337 --> 22:46.861
What are you doing
in here?

22:53.781 --> 22:56.218
Couldn't sleep
with the hammering.

22:56.262 --> 22:58.090
Why are you
in here?

22:58.133 --> 22:59.439
It can't be helping.

23:00.527 --> 23:04.749
I need something
to occupy my mind.

23:04.792 --> 23:07.316
I didn't
solve it before.

23:07.360 --> 23:08.970
Maybe I can now.

23:10.102 --> 23:12.670
Are you still
seeing things?

23:13.888 --> 23:15.673
[Clanging]

23:15.716 --> 23:17.239
They're still
at it.

23:17.283 --> 23:19.372
♪

23:19.416 --> 23:20.939
You check
the radio lately?No.

23:20.982 --> 23:22.375
It'll hold.

23:22.419 --> 23:24.246
Maybe we should leave,
June.

23:24.290 --> 23:25.509
[Clanging continues]

23:25.552 --> 23:27.554
No one was meant
to be down here.

23:27.598 --> 23:29.991
You tore the suit.

23:30.035 --> 23:31.689
And you saw it
up there.

23:31.732 --> 23:33.299
Getting through
that fallout,

23:33.342 --> 23:34.735
that is not going to be
an easy journey,

23:34.779 --> 23:36.084
let alone
getting through them.

23:36.128 --> 23:37.434
And in
the condition you're in,

23:37.477 --> 23:38.957
I don't think
we'd make it very far,

23:39.000 --> 23:41.176
or if we did, the radiation
would kill us in days.

23:41.220 --> 23:42.787
[Clanging continues]

23:42.830 --> 23:45.006
You know,
a lot of people find it easier

23:45.050 --> 23:48.575
to go through what you're
going through with medication.

23:48.619 --> 23:51.317
There are sedatives
in the first-aid kit.

23:52.274 --> 23:55.060
Well,
would it put me to sleep?For a couple days.

23:55.103 --> 23:57.410
Until you're through
the worst of it.Are you sure
that's smart?

23:57.454 --> 24:00.239
I mean, what if those folks
manage to pry the hatch open?

24:00.282 --> 24:04.504
John, I know it is really hard
to be down here.

24:04.548 --> 24:07.376
It's really hard
to be reminded of what he did.

24:07.420 --> 24:08.769
That's not
what this is.

24:08.813 --> 24:10.249
Then what is this
really about, John?

24:10.292 --> 24:11.859
Why do you want to run out
into a world

24:11.903 --> 24:13.687
that's going to kill you
in 10 different ways?

24:15.297 --> 24:17.735
I know
you think you saw her.

24:17.778 --> 24:20.477
But I don't think she's the one
that's not at peace, John.

24:20.520 --> 24:22.391
I think that's you, and whatever
you are seeing in here,

24:22.435 --> 24:23.828
that's coming from you,

24:23.871 --> 24:25.960
and you are not going to fix it
by leaving.

24:26.004 --> 24:28.397
[Creaking]

24:28.441 --> 24:31.400
♪

24:31.444 --> 24:34.099
Right.

24:34.142 --> 24:37.015
♪

24:37.058 --> 24:40.061
There is something else
that might make this easier.

24:40.105 --> 24:42.934
What's that?

24:52.813 --> 24:55.207
Get some sleep.

24:57.122 --> 24:59.211
[Sighs]

24:59.254 --> 25:01.474
That's a tall order.

25:01.518 --> 25:03.432
One of us
should stay awake,

25:03.476 --> 25:05.217
in case
things get hairy.

25:05.260 --> 25:07.219
[Chalk squeaks]

25:07.262 --> 25:09.700
[Lantern clanging]

25:16.445 --> 25:18.665
[John sighs]

25:21.146 --> 25:23.278
[Banging]

25:23.322 --> 25:27.021
[The Mamas and the Papas'
"California Dreamin'"plays]

25:27.065 --> 25:32.461
♪

25:32.505 --> 25:34.812
Cindy:
You can't stay here.

25:34.855 --> 25:38.511
♪

25:38.555 --> 25:40.034
You're just
in my head.

25:40.078 --> 25:41.688
Cindy: Am I?

25:41.732 --> 25:45.039
Look at
what he's doing to me.

25:45.083 --> 25:47.128
Stop. Stop!

25:47.172 --> 25:49.783
You know
how to do that.

25:49.827 --> 25:52.046
♪

25:52.090 --> 25:54.658
Find me.

25:54.701 --> 25:56.268
♪

25:56.311 --> 25:58.618
God damn it!

25:58.662 --> 26:02.230
[Banging continues]

26:02.274 --> 26:05.494
[Wood creaking]

26:07.148 --> 26:09.063
John...

26:09.107 --> 26:10.674
John.

26:11.544 --> 26:13.677
Don't do that!
I have to!

26:13.720 --> 26:14.982
You're gonna bring
the whole place down!

26:15.026 --> 26:17.028
I need to get her to stop.
I can do it in there.

26:17.071 --> 26:18.595
You're not
thinking straight!

26:18.638 --> 26:21.162
The answer's in there!
I find it, she'll leave me be.

26:21.206 --> 26:22.686
Then I'll be able
to think straight.

26:22.729 --> 26:24.862
Be able
to deal with them.

26:24.905 --> 26:29.736
♪

26:29.780 --> 26:31.433
Aah! What the hell
are you doing?!

26:31.477 --> 26:34.132
June...You...

26:34.175 --> 26:36.090
I'm sorry, but I should have
done that sooner.

26:36.134 --> 26:37.309
You'll just --

26:37.352 --> 26:38.702
[Wood creaking]

26:38.745 --> 26:41.313
John!

26:41.356 --> 26:43.489
♪

26:47.362 --> 26:49.582
Voice over radio:
We know that place ain't

26:49.626 --> 26:52.672
gonna hold up much longer.

26:52.716 --> 26:55.719
We know you're listening...

26:55.762 --> 26:59.331
so consider this
your final warning.

27:04.597 --> 27:07.513
Dorie Sr.: June?

27:07.556 --> 27:08.862
June?

27:11.430 --> 27:13.867
[Grunts]

27:17.262 --> 27:19.525
[Grunts]

27:19.568 --> 27:26.184
♪

27:26.227 --> 27:29.143
June.

27:29.187 --> 27:30.754
June.

27:30.797 --> 27:33.974
Cindy:
She's still breathing.

27:34.018 --> 27:35.759
♪

27:35.802 --> 27:37.325
I'm not.

27:37.369 --> 27:38.892
♪

27:38.936 --> 27:40.372
June, wake up.

27:40.415 --> 27:41.895
She tried
to drug you.

27:41.939 --> 27:43.549
It's what Teddy did
to me.

27:43.592 --> 27:47.074
John, please.

27:47.118 --> 27:50.164
♪

27:50.208 --> 27:51.557
[Creaking]

27:51.600 --> 27:54.212
♪

27:54.255 --> 27:55.648
I can't
leave her here.

27:55.692 --> 27:57.606
It's not
going to collapse.

27:57.650 --> 27:59.217
They're not
going to get in.

27:59.260 --> 28:02.655
Teddy told me he built it
to withstand a nuclear blast.

28:02.699 --> 28:07.181
He told me that's why
no one would hear me scream.

28:07.225 --> 28:09.401
♪

28:09.444 --> 28:11.359
Help me.

28:11.403 --> 28:13.144
Then help her.

28:13.187 --> 28:22.806
♪

28:22.849 --> 28:24.764
Where did he
take you from?

28:24.808 --> 28:26.157
I don't know.

28:26.200 --> 28:28.028
I always thought
he took you

28:28.072 --> 28:30.596
from the diner parking lot
after your shift.

28:30.639 --> 28:32.467
We turned that place over
looking for you.

28:32.511 --> 28:35.383
But if -- if he took you
from somewhere else...

28:35.427 --> 28:37.864
then that's where
he woulda dumped you.

28:37.908 --> 28:40.214
That's where
your body would've been.

28:40.258 --> 28:43.652
Where, John?

28:43.696 --> 28:45.654
June: John...

28:45.698 --> 28:46.873
John?She's awake.

28:46.917 --> 28:48.266
She can
take care of herself.

28:48.309 --> 28:50.224
I can't.

28:50.268 --> 28:52.661
[Groans] John...

28:52.705 --> 28:55.055
John?

28:55.099 --> 28:58.667
I didn't know
you were wearing this.

28:58.711 --> 29:01.540
I-I-I didn't want
to lose it at work.

29:01.583 --> 29:03.063
I only wore it
when I was seeing my boyfriend.

29:03.107 --> 29:04.282
I know.

29:04.325 --> 29:06.501
That's what
he told us.

29:06.545 --> 29:09.200
Were you on your way to see him
when Teddy nabbed you?

29:09.243 --> 29:11.811
Maybe.

29:11.855 --> 29:15.075
Then that's
where he dumped you.

29:15.119 --> 29:17.904
There -- that's where
your boyfriend lived,

29:17.948 --> 29:19.645
across from
that abandoned lot.

29:19.688 --> 29:21.212
I remember going there
to talk to him.

29:21.255 --> 29:23.214
Then that's where I am.

29:23.257 --> 29:28.480
♪

29:28.523 --> 29:31.091
[Groans]

29:31.135 --> 29:33.572
♪

29:33.615 --> 29:36.096
[Groans]
June.

29:36.140 --> 29:37.228
John...

29:37.271 --> 29:39.012
I know where she is, June.
I gotta go.

29:39.056 --> 29:40.361
John,
it's not safe out there.

29:40.405 --> 29:41.972
Those people,
they are -- they're back,

29:42.015 --> 29:43.756
and that radiation alone
is enough to kill you.

29:43.800 --> 29:45.149
She sure about that?

29:45.192 --> 29:46.454
If they're still alive,

29:46.498 --> 29:49.501
it's not as dangerous
as she said.

29:49.544 --> 29:51.242
Is she right?

29:51.285 --> 29:52.765
Who?

29:52.809 --> 29:54.375
I don't know
what you're talking about, John.

29:54.419 --> 29:55.681
You need to rest.

29:55.724 --> 29:57.683
They're alive.

29:57.726 --> 29:59.598
Did he sound sick
to you?

29:59.641 --> 30:01.600
Is it really as dangerous
as you said?

30:01.643 --> 30:03.950
I-I-I-I don't know.

30:03.994 --> 30:05.343
What do you mean
you don't know?!

30:05.386 --> 30:07.388
Where did all those numbers
on the board come from?!

30:07.432 --> 30:10.783
Why do we have to wait
294 more days?!I can explain, John!

30:11.871 --> 30:13.786
I thought you said
you got it out of that book.

30:13.830 --> 30:15.396
John,
listen to me, okay?

30:15.440 --> 30:16.702
I did
what I had to.

30:16.745 --> 30:17.964
She's lying,
John.

30:18.008 --> 30:19.836
Are they in there
or not?

30:19.879 --> 30:21.925
I was being safe!
Now cut me loose!

30:21.968 --> 30:23.578
Not until
you tell me the truth!

30:23.622 --> 30:25.798
Tell me the truth!
Tell me!

30:25.842 --> 30:27.844
I-I made them up.

30:28.801 --> 30:29.976
You see?

30:30.020 --> 30:33.501
I told you.
Why?!

30:33.545 --> 30:35.939
I don't want
to go up there.

30:35.982 --> 30:37.723
You shouldn't,
either.

30:37.766 --> 30:39.159
She lied to you.

30:39.203 --> 30:41.945
It's not about the radiation,
is it?

30:41.988 --> 30:44.948
I know what to expect down here
every day.

30:44.991 --> 30:47.167
I know what
it's supposed to look like.

30:47.211 --> 30:50.170
Up there, I don't know
what anything looks like.

30:50.214 --> 30:51.955
None of us do.That's not
what I mean.

30:51.998 --> 30:55.001
I mean without John.

30:55.045 --> 30:57.656
[Clanging]

30:59.658 --> 31:03.792
You don't want to leave,
you don't have to.

31:06.012 --> 31:08.188
John, don't go out there.
John!

31:08.232 --> 31:12.149
[Rumbling]

31:12.192 --> 31:14.934
[Groans] John!

31:14.978 --> 31:18.590
[Fabric rustling]

31:18.633 --> 31:21.245
Where are you going?

31:21.288 --> 31:23.769
To keep the only damn promise
I ever made

31:23.812 --> 31:25.031
that I can still keep.

31:25.075 --> 31:28.339
John, no.
No, do not go out there.

31:28.382 --> 31:30.602
I know
where he dumped her, June.

31:30.645 --> 31:32.125
I can
put her to rest.

31:32.169 --> 31:33.779
That was
40 years ago.

31:33.822 --> 31:36.651
John, there is nothing left
up there.

31:36.695 --> 31:40.220
I'mout there, John.

31:40.264 --> 31:42.005
Find me.

31:44.007 --> 31:49.012
♪

31:49.055 --> 31:52.667
[Rumbling]

31:52.711 --> 31:54.060
I'll come back
for you.

31:54.104 --> 31:55.583
The hatch'll hold.

31:55.627 --> 31:56.976
Just let me free her.

31:57.020 --> 31:58.456
Then I'll free you.

31:58.499 --> 31:59.805
John,
don't go up there.

31:59.848 --> 32:01.241
You almost died
last time.

32:01.285 --> 32:03.461
If those people on the radio
don't kill you,

32:03.504 --> 32:04.810
the dead will.

32:04.853 --> 32:07.421
We're already living
6 feet underground.

32:07.465 --> 32:10.207
I'm not sure
I see what the difference is.

32:10.250 --> 32:13.819
♪

32:17.431 --> 32:23.437
[Breathing heavily]

32:42.674 --> 32:45.024
Which way?

32:45.068 --> 32:47.418
Where are you when I need you?

32:47.461 --> 32:49.898
[Breathing heavily]

32:53.859 --> 32:55.904
[Clattering]

32:55.948 --> 32:59.212
[Grunts]

32:59.256 --> 33:03.173
[Clanging]

33:13.139 --> 33:15.272
[Clanging]

33:15.315 --> 33:21.930
♪

33:21.974 --> 33:24.107
No.

33:24.150 --> 33:26.152
♪

33:26.196 --> 33:27.980
Cindy:
They can't get in.

33:28.024 --> 33:29.590
They'll still be trying
when you get back.

33:29.634 --> 33:32.115
John,
what are you doing?

33:32.158 --> 33:34.334
You have to find me.Why are you
confusing me?

33:34.378 --> 33:36.032
Because you promised.You're not real.

33:36.075 --> 33:37.555
So how do you know
they are?

33:37.598 --> 33:38.904
I know she is.

33:38.947 --> 33:40.253
June's real.
I can't leave her.

33:40.297 --> 33:42.473
You do that,
they are gonna come after you.

33:42.516 --> 33:44.779
You won't be able
to keep your promise to me.

33:44.823 --> 33:46.912
I have to help her.You have to help me.

33:46.955 --> 33:49.175
She's still alive.
I can save her.
You can't.

33:49.219 --> 33:50.959
John, you can't even
save yourself.

33:51.003 --> 33:52.744
I can.
John...

33:52.787 --> 33:54.572
John.

33:54.615 --> 33:56.748
John!

33:56.791 --> 34:01.579
♪

34:01.622 --> 34:02.884
[Gunshot]

34:02.928 --> 34:04.364
[Gunshots]

34:04.408 --> 34:11.763
♪

34:11.806 --> 34:13.852
[Gunfire]

34:13.895 --> 34:20.641
♪

34:20.685 --> 34:23.905
Don't break
your promise.

34:23.949 --> 34:26.604
[Gunshots]

34:26.647 --> 34:28.997
I'm not.

34:29.041 --> 34:36.048
♪

34:36.092 --> 34:37.397
You'll never
get them all.

34:37.441 --> 34:38.790
Don't give me
something to prove.

34:38.833 --> 34:41.358
[Gunshots]

34:41.401 --> 34:51.324
♪

34:51.368 --> 34:57.635
♪

34:57.678 --> 35:00.551
[Grunts]

35:00.594 --> 35:02.770
[Footsteps]

35:02.814 --> 35:05.469
♪

35:05.512 --> 35:07.775
No. No!

35:07.819 --> 35:17.394
♪

35:17.437 --> 35:22.312
♪

35:22.355 --> 35:25.619
[Wind whistling]

35:25.663 --> 35:35.063
♪

35:35.107 --> 35:36.413
Why are you doing this?

35:36.456 --> 35:38.850
Because you didn't
stop him.

35:38.893 --> 35:42.288
Because he still
destroyed everything.

35:42.332 --> 35:44.595
Please --
I have to help her.

35:44.638 --> 35:45.900
You can't.

35:45.944 --> 35:48.903
She'll be another dead body
in the ground.

35:48.947 --> 35:51.428
Just like us.

35:51.471 --> 35:53.081
[Indistinct whispering]

35:53.125 --> 35:55.823
You're not real.

35:55.867 --> 35:57.434
You're not real.

35:57.477 --> 35:59.697
You're not real.

35:59.740 --> 36:01.220
You're not real.

36:01.264 --> 36:11.056
♪

36:11.099 --> 36:14.320
♪

36:14.364 --> 36:17.280
[Walkers growling]

36:17.323 --> 36:26.463
♪

36:26.506 --> 36:36.342
♪

36:36.386 --> 36:40.912
[Walkers growling]

36:40.955 --> 36:49.921
♪

36:49.964 --> 36:52.532
It's not real.

36:52.576 --> 36:54.055
It's not real.

36:54.099 --> 36:55.448
It's not real!

36:55.492 --> 36:57.102
[Growling continues]

36:57.145 --> 37:06.633
♪

37:06.677 --> 37:08.156
♪

37:08.200 --> 37:09.593
Man:
You coming out?

37:09.636 --> 37:11.725
Or are you gonna make me
come in there?

37:11.769 --> 37:14.902
♪

37:14.946 --> 37:17.165
[Gun cocks]

37:17.209 --> 37:22.388
♪

37:22.432 --> 37:23.998
[Gunshot]

37:24.042 --> 37:25.304
[Body thuds]

37:26.914 --> 37:28.786
You okay?

37:28.829 --> 37:30.657
Yeah. You?

37:30.701 --> 37:32.398
Yeah.

37:32.442 --> 37:35.619
I gotta tell you --
you're right.

37:35.662 --> 37:39.187
That's some real ugly mustard
up there.

37:39.231 --> 37:45.019
♪

37:45.063 --> 37:47.718
John...

37:47.761 --> 37:56.204
♪

37:56.248 --> 37:58.859
I can't believe
it's her.

37:58.903 --> 38:02.036
He musta still had her here
when we were closing in on him.

38:02.080 --> 38:06.258
Musta been too spooked to pose
her where he found her, so...

38:06.302 --> 38:08.347
he buried her
in the wall.

38:08.391 --> 38:10.262
♪

38:10.306 --> 38:12.612
You kept your promise.

38:12.656 --> 38:14.875
She's at rest now.

38:14.919 --> 38:16.007
Not yet.

38:16.050 --> 38:26.017
♪

38:26.060 --> 38:32.023
♪

38:32.066 --> 38:34.025
[Creaking]

38:34.068 --> 38:37.245
Better get a move on.

38:41.685 --> 38:44.252
I know
you don't wanna go up there.

38:45.341 --> 38:47.386
But I'm afraid you don't have
much choice.

38:48.909 --> 38:51.695
No, I don't.

38:52.870 --> 38:55.263
I'll help you see
which way is up, then.

38:55.307 --> 38:57.048
'Cause I think
I see it again.

39:04.316 --> 39:08.494
♪

39:08.538 --> 39:10.844
I'll be
right behind ya.

39:10.888 --> 39:13.717
[Rumbling]

39:15.849 --> 39:18.722
Move! Go! Move!It's not gonna hold,
John!

39:18.765 --> 39:20.985
Ohh!

39:21.028 --> 39:23.422
♪

39:34.520 --> 39:36.653
June: Hey.

39:36.696 --> 39:39.090
You're awake.

39:39.133 --> 39:41.353
You were out
for days.

39:41.397 --> 39:43.442
The collapse
and the DTs --

39:43.486 --> 39:46.445
I was worried
you weren't going to wake up.

39:46.489 --> 39:50.101
Where are we?

39:55.759 --> 39:58.631
Not underground.

40:01.199 --> 40:03.506
How...?

40:03.549 --> 40:05.464
Someone heard
your radio messages.

40:05.508 --> 40:07.684
We survived
because we had the masks on

40:07.727 --> 40:08.902
when
the dirt collapsed.

40:08.946 --> 40:10.382
[Scoffs]

40:10.426 --> 40:11.688
I'll be.

40:12.819 --> 40:14.778
John,
the only reason I am alive

40:14.821 --> 40:17.171
is because
you talked me into leaving.

40:17.215 --> 40:18.956
Well...

40:18.999 --> 40:21.306
I just wanted to help you
see which way was up.

40:21.349 --> 40:23.700
Well, here, it's...[Knock on door]

40:23.743 --> 40:25.353
...pretty clear.

40:25.397 --> 40:28.705
Just not
what we thought it'd be.

40:28.748 --> 40:31.490
[Door opens]

40:33.013 --> 40:35.755
Well,
good morning.

40:35.799 --> 40:37.322
Victor.

40:37.365 --> 40:38.932
June: He wanted to know
as soon as you were up.

40:38.976 --> 40:40.412
How'd you survive
all this?

40:40.456 --> 40:41.761
Better than you did.

40:41.805 --> 40:44.938
But that's gonna change
now that you're here.

40:47.593 --> 40:49.552
You think
we're gonna join you

40:49.595 --> 40:51.467
after what you did to Morgan
at the sub?

40:55.035 --> 40:57.385
I, um...

40:57.429 --> 41:01.172
I did
what I did, yes.

41:01.215 --> 41:03.130
But I'm here.

41:03.174 --> 41:05.176
Morgan's out there.

41:06.743 --> 41:09.354
Doesn't make it right.

41:10.442 --> 41:13.576
But it does make staying here
your only choice.

41:13.619 --> 41:14.838
He's right.
We can't go out there,

41:14.881 --> 41:16.274
not in
the condition you're in.

41:16.317 --> 41:18.276
Not in the condition
everything out there is in.

41:19.364 --> 41:22.976
You have any idea who those
people in the gas masks are?

41:24.630 --> 41:27.067
I've been asking myself
the same question.

41:27.111 --> 41:29.287
Perhaps we can
answer it together,

41:29.330 --> 41:33.204
assuming that your skills
at detection are as...

41:33.247 --> 41:36.207
fantastic as I've heard them
to be.

41:39.079 --> 41:40.211
[Sighs]

41:40.254 --> 41:42.169
To new beginnings.

41:42.213 --> 41:45.390
To whatever's next.

41:51.831 --> 41:54.181
No, thanks.

41:55.095 --> 41:56.575
I'm, uh...

41:56.619 --> 41:59.578
I'm off the sauce
right now.

41:59.622 --> 42:01.101
Mm.

42:05.323 --> 42:08.239
Maybe later.

42:09.327 --> 42:10.894
I assume you have
many questions,

42:10.937 --> 42:12.635
but for now,
you should rest.

42:12.678 --> 42:17.248
The grand tour
is still to come.

42:20.120 --> 42:21.252
[Door closes]

42:21.295 --> 42:23.123
We can't stay here.

42:23.167 --> 42:25.256
I'd rather face
whatever's out there.

42:28.694 --> 42:31.697
[Walkers growling]

42:31.741 --> 42:34.918
Leaving really isn't
an option.

42:37.485 --> 42:43.056
Maybe I shoulda taken him up
on that drink.

42:46.582 --> 42:50.673
[Walkers growling]

42:53.719 --> 42:56.809
Hey!

42:58.115 --> 43:00.508
Hey!

43:02.119 --> 43:03.947
June?

43:03.990 --> 43:05.122
Mr. Dorie, can you hear me?

43:05.165 --> 43:06.602
It's Morgan.

43:06.645 --> 43:07.951
I heard your message
on the radio.

43:07.994 --> 43:10.693
I need you to tell me
if you're down there.

43:12.695 --> 43:14.871
June!

43:14.914 --> 43:17.787
Strand:
They're not.

43:19.397 --> 43:21.529
Victor?
Where are they?

43:21.573 --> 43:24.141
They're with me.
And they're safe.

43:24.184 --> 43:26.534
Which is more
than you'd be able to say

43:26.578 --> 43:28.145
if you'd
found them first.

43:28.188 --> 43:29.363
You listen to me.

43:29.407 --> 43:31.409
You need
to tell me where they are.

43:31.452 --> 43:33.019
You're such a bore.

43:33.063 --> 43:35.848
How about we do this every night
so you can put me to sleep?

43:35.892 --> 43:37.154
[Chuckles]

43:37.197 --> 43:39.330
I'm done listening to you,
Morgan.

43:39.373 --> 43:40.897
Everyone is.

43:40.940 --> 43:42.681
Everyone tried it your way
and look what happened.

43:42.725 --> 43:43.987
Death.

43:44.030 --> 43:45.902
Destruction.

43:45.945 --> 43:49.166
Face the truth, Morgan --
you failed.

43:49.209 --> 43:50.689
You're a failure.

43:50.733 --> 43:52.560
We are here...

43:52.604 --> 43:54.780
because of
what youdid.

43:54.824 --> 43:57.304
I don't see it
that way.

43:57.348 --> 43:59.742
And now it's my turn.

43:59.785 --> 44:01.744
I'm going to do
what you couldn't.

44:01.787 --> 44:03.963
I'm going to rebuild
the world.

44:04.007 --> 44:07.314
I'm going to help everyone
that you let down.

44:07.358 --> 44:09.969
Well,
the ones that I see fit.

44:10.013 --> 44:13.320
All while you watch
from the outside.

44:13.364 --> 44:14.974
I hope you do.

44:15.018 --> 44:16.584
I didn't think you'd give up
so easily.

44:16.628 --> 44:18.151
I'm not finished.

44:18.195 --> 44:21.589
You should rebuild the world,
Victor.

44:21.633 --> 44:23.766
You should help people.

44:23.809 --> 44:25.942
I'm not gonna stop you
from doing that.

44:25.985 --> 44:28.640
But if I hear
that is not what you're doing,

44:28.684 --> 44:31.643
if I hear that you've hurt
anybody that I care about,

44:31.687 --> 44:33.123
I swear to God --

44:33.166 --> 44:35.516
What, Morgan?
What?

44:35.560 --> 44:36.909
♪

44:36.953 --> 44:38.737
I will come for you,
Victor.

44:38.781 --> 44:40.391
And I will do

44:40.434 --> 44:43.786
what you tried to do to me
on that submarine.

44:43.829 --> 44:47.311
Only I won't miss.

44:47.354 --> 44:56.755
♪

44:56.799 --> 44:58.975
Bring it.

44:59.018 --> 45:08.985
♪

45:09.028 --> 45:18.603
♪

45:21.519 --> 45:22.738
[Walkers growling]

45:24.914 --> 45:25.958
So many dead.

45:26.002 --> 45:27.046
[Gun cocks]

45:27.090 --> 45:28.265
Man: Step away
from my brother.

45:28.308 --> 45:29.788
[Chuckles]

45:29.832 --> 45:32.095
You bringing strays
to my doorstep?

45:32.138 --> 45:34.314
You're gonna
help me find Mr. Jones.

45:34.358 --> 45:35.751
What makes you think

45:35.794 --> 45:37.970
you're gonna do
what your brother couldn't?

45:38.014 --> 45:39.580
♪

45:39.624 --> 45:41.060
Morgan,
you there?

45:41.104 --> 45:43.019
[Walkers growling]

45:43.062 --> 45:50.461
♪

45:51.462 --> 45:53.507
♪

45:53.551 --> 45:57.076
Chambliss: This episode
is called "Cindy Hawkins."

45:57.120 --> 46:00.036
That title actually
comes from the name

46:00.079 --> 46:02.429
of one of Teddy's victims,

46:02.473 --> 46:05.519
a victim who, we'll learn
over the course of the episode,

46:05.563 --> 46:08.871
actually holds a lot of
significance to John Dorie Sr.

46:08.914 --> 46:12.265
Keep your promise.

46:12.309 --> 46:14.398
Find me.

46:14.441 --> 46:17.357
♪

46:17.401 --> 46:19.446
The beginning of this sequence
really was about showing

46:19.490 --> 46:21.579
what life is like
in this fall-out bunker,

46:21.622 --> 46:24.321
and even though the world above
has gone to hell,

46:24.364 --> 46:26.976
they actually have something
that's not all that bad.

46:27.019 --> 46:29.369
We kind of see the two of them
creating this bond

46:29.413 --> 46:30.762
where they're growing
close together,

46:30.806 --> 46:31.850
where they're actually
with family,

46:31.894 --> 46:33.025
the family neither one of them,

46:33.069 --> 46:34.331
I think, ever thought
they would have.

46:34.374 --> 46:35.854
I know
I'm not the Dorie

46:35.898 --> 46:37.769
you thought you'd be
spending your days with.

46:37.813 --> 46:39.902
I am happy to be
where I am.

46:39.945 --> 46:41.860
♪

46:41.904 --> 46:43.383
This bunker is actually

46:43.427 --> 46:47.126
where Teddy killed all the women
back in the '70s.

46:47.170 --> 46:49.737
When John Dorie Sr.
discovers the room

46:49.781 --> 46:52.131
where Teddy killed everyone,

46:52.175 --> 46:54.960
not only is he kind of reminded
of his own failures

46:55.004 --> 46:57.093
in stopping Teddy in the past,

46:57.136 --> 46:59.573
but he's reminded of a promise
that he made

46:59.617 --> 47:01.749
to one of Teddy's victims.

47:01.793 --> 47:03.142
Cindy Hawkins.

47:03.186 --> 47:04.883
I looked that girl's mama
square in the eye,

47:04.927 --> 47:07.190
and I promised her I'd help give
her the ending she deserved.

47:07.233 --> 47:10.149
40 years later,
he thinks he's going to

47:10.193 --> 47:12.195
finally make good
on his promise.

47:12.238 --> 47:18.114
As Dorie Sr. continues to see
visions of Cindy Hawkins,

47:18.157 --> 47:20.507
the one thing
that Cindy starts to do --

47:20.551 --> 47:22.814
and, really,
is John's subconscious --

47:22.858 --> 47:24.860
is start to turn him
against June.

47:24.903 --> 47:27.558
John, have you been drinking
without me knowing?

47:27.601 --> 47:28.559
Here and there.

47:28.602 --> 47:30.430
As June discovers,

47:30.474 --> 47:35.218
Dorie Sr. has actually been
secretly drinking in the bunker.

47:35.261 --> 47:38.961
And now he's without the one
thing he used to self-medicate,

47:39.004 --> 47:43.226
and it comes at the moment when
he is quite literally haunted

47:43.269 --> 47:46.577
by the one victim
he wasn't able to give peace to.

47:46.620 --> 47:48.622
John...

47:48.666 --> 47:50.363
John,
don't do that!
I have to!

47:50.407 --> 47:51.799
You're gonna bring
the whole place down!

47:51.843 --> 47:53.236
I need to get her to stop.

47:53.279 --> 47:55.238
Dorie is going to risk
both of their lives

47:55.281 --> 47:56.674
to go up above ground,

47:56.717 --> 47:59.155
and June feels like
the only thing she can do

47:59.198 --> 48:01.766
to protect themselves
is to sedate him

48:01.809 --> 48:02.985
until he gets through, really,

48:03.028 --> 48:05.117
the worst
of his alcohol withdrawal.

48:05.161 --> 48:07.903
June...You...

48:07.946 --> 48:09.774
I'm sorry, but I should have
done that sooner.

48:09.817 --> 48:10.818
You'll just --

48:10.862 --> 48:12.472
[Wood creaking]

48:12.516 --> 48:14.997
June! June

48:15.040 --> 48:20.872
♪

48:20.916 --> 48:23.396
Ultimately, this experience

48:23.440 --> 48:25.572
where John tries
to go above ground

48:25.616 --> 48:27.487
when June wants to stay
below ground

48:27.531 --> 48:30.534
leads to the reveal from June

48:30.577 --> 48:32.666
that she was actually lying
about how long they needed

48:32.710 --> 48:35.495
to stay in the bunker before it
was safe to go above ground.

48:35.539 --> 48:37.497
Is it really as dangerous
as you said?

48:37.541 --> 48:39.978
I-I-I-I don't know.

48:40.022 --> 48:42.720
Tell me the truth!
Tell me!

48:42.763 --> 48:43.808
I-I made them up.

48:43.851 --> 48:45.984
Why?!

48:46.028 --> 48:48.247
I don't want
to go up there.

48:48.291 --> 48:50.206
even without John.

48:50.249 --> 48:53.035
That reveal forces June

48:53.078 --> 48:55.037
to admit
that it's actually rooted

48:55.080 --> 48:57.865
in kind of a deep-seated fear
she has...

48:57.909 --> 49:00.520
♪

49:00.564 --> 49:03.567
...the unknown that she's
going to face in terms of

49:03.610 --> 49:07.223
what a world looks like
without John Dorie Jr. in it.

49:07.266 --> 49:12.750
♪

49:12.793 --> 49:14.926
Where are you going?

49:14.970 --> 49:16.493
To keep the only damn promise

49:16.536 --> 49:18.147
I ever made
that I can still keep.

49:18.190 --> 49:22.629
Dorie Sr. kind of once again
choosing the investigation

49:22.673 --> 49:24.501
over his own family.

49:24.544 --> 49:26.155
John, don't go out there.
John!

49:26.198 --> 49:29.506
He's ready to leave June behind,
who's in some real danger

49:29.549 --> 49:33.292
because she's pinned beneath
a collapsed beam in this bunker.

49:33.336 --> 49:34.946
He's going above ground

49:34.990 --> 49:37.253
because he thinks he can solve
the crime once more.

49:37.296 --> 49:39.037
You have to find me.Why are you
confusing me?

49:39.081 --> 49:40.125
You're not real.

49:40.169 --> 49:41.692
So how do you know
they are?

49:41.735 --> 49:42.693
I know she is.

49:42.736 --> 49:44.303
June's real.
I can't leave her.

49:44.347 --> 49:46.305
♪

49:46.349 --> 49:48.177
No. No!

49:48.220 --> 49:51.963
Chambliss: After John Dorie Sr.
makes the right decision

49:52.007 --> 49:54.183
and he returns to the bunker

49:54.226 --> 49:57.316
and does it with just
enough time to save June

49:57.360 --> 49:59.753
from the stalker
who's infiltrated,

49:59.797 --> 50:01.625
they actually end up finding

50:01.668 --> 50:04.889
that Cindy Hawkins was buried
in the walls of the bunker,

50:04.932 --> 50:07.457
that Teddy
must have not had enough time

50:07.500 --> 50:09.850
to put her body anywhere else.

50:09.894 --> 50:12.288
And ultimately, Dorie Sr.

50:12.331 --> 50:14.638
is able to kind
of fulfill the promise

50:14.681 --> 50:18.337
that he made to Cindy Hawkins'
mother all those years ago.

50:18.381 --> 50:22.820
♪

50:22.863 --> 50:24.387
I think he realizes

50:24.430 --> 50:26.345
that it's never too late
to forgive himself,

50:26.389 --> 50:29.740
that it's never too late
to put his past behind him

50:29.783 --> 50:31.176
and embrace the present

50:31.220 --> 50:33.222
instead of kind of
dwelling in the past.

50:33.265 --> 50:35.354
I'll help you see
which way is up, then.

50:35.398 --> 50:37.008
'Cause I think
I see it again.

50:37.052 --> 50:40.446
It's that lesson that he's gonna
exit this bunker with.

50:40.490 --> 50:42.361
Move! Go! Move!It's not gonna hold,
John!

50:42.405 --> 50:44.537
Ohh!

50:44.581 --> 50:46.974
♪

50:51.283 --> 50:54.808
The difference in June
and Dorie Sr.'s reactions

50:54.852 --> 50:56.375
to living in Strand's tower

50:56.419 --> 50:58.247
really are kind of a function
of the fact

50:58.290 --> 50:59.987
that she's had
some time to accept

51:00.031 --> 51:02.947
that this may be the only way
they're gonna be able to live.

51:02.990 --> 51:04.775
Well,
good morning.

51:04.818 --> 51:05.863
Victor.

51:05.906 --> 51:07.604
Dorie Sr. is waking up into this

51:07.647 --> 51:09.214
and is kind of
discovering the fact

51:09.258 --> 51:11.390
that they are now
forced to live with the man

51:11.434 --> 51:13.392
who he saw do
some pretty terrible things.

51:13.436 --> 51:15.655
I'm done listening to you,
Morgan.

51:15.699 --> 51:17.048
I'm going to do
what you couldn't.

51:17.092 --> 51:19.442
I'm going to rebuild
the world.

51:19.485 --> 51:22.053
I'm going to help everyone
that you let down.

51:22.097 --> 51:25.796
Strand is reallyenjoying the
fact that he is the leader now

51:25.839 --> 51:27.885
and Morgan's on the outs.

51:27.928 --> 51:30.366
I think in many ways it really
speaks to

51:30.409 --> 51:34.674
Strand's need
to kind of be recognized,

51:34.718 --> 51:37.851
and that's a big part
of what his journey's gonna be

51:37.895 --> 51:39.766
as we continue to go forward
in the season.

51:39.810 --> 51:42.465
I will come for you,
Victor.

51:42.508 --> 51:44.162
Bring it.

51:44.206 --> 51:46.904
It really is kind of setting up
this antagonism

51:46.947 --> 51:48.427
between these two characters

51:48.471 --> 51:50.908
as we continue to go
deeper into the season,

51:50.951 --> 51:52.388
and I think
it creates a question of,

51:52.431 --> 51:54.477
"Whose side
is everyone gonna fall onto

51:54.520 --> 51:56.435
as the conflict continues?"

51:56.479 --> 52:01.266
♪

52:04.051 --> 52:13.800
♪

52:13.844 --> 52:23.810
♪

52:23.854 --> 52:31.862
♪
